===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[dies Jovis]]'' ("day of Jupiter") through Indian astrology in the fifth century as Sanskrit ''[[bṝhaspativāra]]'' (''bṝhaspati'', "the regent of the planet Jupiter") into Buddhist astrology in the 8th century as 木曜日: [[木]] (もく, ''moku'', "wood", the Buddhist element associated with the planet Jupiter) + [[曜日]] (ようび, ''yōbi'', "day of the week").

===Noun===
{{janoun|もくようび|mokuyōbi}}
# [[Thursday]]

